AB  - This paper examines the monetary approach to the balance of payments under fixed exchange rates when domestic prices and wage rates are not fully flexible. This leads to a formulation in the spirit of a ‘disequilibrium analysis’. We analyze alternatively the cases where the prices of nontraded goods or the nominal wage rate are treated as state variables along with the stock of money. The properties of these systems are analyzed from the point of view of the momentary equilibrium and of the dynamic adjustment process.
